==English==

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɑː(r)n|-ɑː(r)n]]

===Noun===
'''barn'''  (''plural:'' '''[[barns]]''')
# A [[building]], often found on a [[farm]], used for storage or keeping animals such as [[cattle]].
# (''nuclear physics'') A [[unit]] of [[surface area]] equal to 10<sup>-28</sup> [[square metre]]s.
# (''slang'') Short for [[barnacle]], A barn is a person who latches on to another person (called the hull) and thinks he or she is somehow better because of his or her association with the hull.

